For some reason I've not had the passion for livejournal over the last few weeks :S But I think it's back now! ... It's probably because I've been ill and completely stuck with work... and looking after family and friends that have ALSO been ill. Everyone seems to be catching colds and the flu... lovely. Anyway, What have I been up to other then work? Photography! Gigs! I saw Alexisonfire last week - and I'm seeing Fightstar tomorrow! I went to london for the anime expo, which was brilliant, will post pictures sometime if you're all interested? :3 I've been trying more to get out with my family lately too... and last night me and mike had a halloween party, whilst mum was away :D haha. It was so much fun! Too much drink. A lot of toilet paper mummies, hot dogs, more drink, balloons, guitar hero and tekken 6, fireworks and sparklers, long exposure and beautiful new dresses from TOP SHOP! .. Oh looord, they're lovely... and I get discount because of working wih BHS! Woop! So here are the photos from last night!! What have you all been up to? :] Keep me informed, and if any of you have facebook, I'm on there more at the moment - leave your link and I shall find you! Rachel and Kane stayed at mine last night, darren headed off with Lull, tom and loz. Kyle and Helen left a little bit before and katie left just after! Good times :D Today I've relaxed, had a shower.. a work out... in some sense of the word *grins* cooked a hot dog pasta with the left over sausages... and to be greedy Jack and I are havin' an indian takeaway tonight to go with our X Factor results - JLS are performing!!! (and bon jovi) ;D Hey, is X Factor big where you guys are? Yazmin -xxx-

Morning everyone! Sorry i've not updated in a while, I've been shockingly busy with work - We've had a number of shops added into our store which has meant a lot of overtime... which i wasn't paid for *grumbles* anywho. It was Jack's Birthday on Thursday - Jack, Me, Amy Mark, Debbie, Simon, Nan and Grandad went to Frankie and Bennies in whitley to celebrate - we all ate too much, laughed until our cheeks hurt and opened a load of presents - Jack got a lot of money towards moving out and driving lessons... and broken biscuits haha. :] But yeah it was loz's birthday on Saturday, so on the friday between the two birthdays, Jack, myself, loz, gordon and tom all went to Alton Towers. Really long drive lol, but totally worth it. Omg we went on all the rides. Ripsaw, oblivion, the blade, air, nemesis, hex, spinball, rapids, flume - everything and it was BRILLIANT. We all got soaked!!! OH and we dressed up as pirates for a photo shoot :P And then yesterday, saturday we all had a party around Darrens house. Myself, Jack, Loz, Rachel, Kirsty, Kane, Jordan, Tom, Darren and Katie! It was an immense amount of laughter and fun. Katie bought Loz and Jack a penis duel. Photos under the cut, ofcourse, which kept us all entertained for hours. Not to mention horn blowing competitions, face caking, kissing girls, getting wasted, falling down stairs, having conversations sat in a bath tub, whilst someone pees. Wierd. it was just fun. fun fun fun :] And now they're both all grown up and 21! Yazmin -xxx-

Last weekend we had a party at Jacks. Loz threw up. Jordan did too - and then we spent ages trying to find him... then we did... balancing on the side of the bath with his head in the sink... unconcious lol. He slept in the bath tub and the rest of us ate fishcakes at 3 in the morning talking about mcdonalds and how big the universe REALLY is. We came to the conclusion that it is pretty frickin big... and then I saw a shooting star. So I made a wish, but I can't tell you what that wish is or it won't come true! SO. Photos :] I love having memories like these... I love having such a lovely group of friends, who really know how to make you laugh, cheer you up and just banter for the entire night. I've been listening to HIM for the last hour and I wish I'd listened to them more lately. Can't wait for the next album in february... . I've just fallen in love with Ville Valo all over again... Im such a big kid. They look like a band :] Proud of this one sometimes they make a better couple ;] Rach and Kane the most handsome man I've ever come across :] Me, Jack, Loz and Darren painting warhammer Yazmin -xxx-

Everyone went over to darren's for a small get together :] All the lads ended up putting on make-up, it was hilarious. They looked like a tribute band for The Cure *Chuckles* Mearnsie, Laura, Mike, Myself, Darren, Jack and Tom are going to see Inglorious Basterds in portsmouth tonight (at 11:30pm) It's gonna be a late one. Hope you've all enjoyed your weekend! Yazmin -xxx-

Today has been really nice :] Jack and I spent hours playing on Ghostbusters for the playstation 3 last night (until about 12:30) and the only reason we turned it off was to watch this small showing of Enter shikari on channel 4. Anyway, the game is brilliant :] It's fun, a little bit chilling and quite scary in places - it really makes you feel like an involved ghostbuster *Chuckles* You have to learn how to capture and defeat ghosts, whilst recording their data on your ghost database. What I really liked is thta they refered to so many of the ghosts from the films! but yeah - this morning we went down into town, got a shakeaways milkshake and then headed to see Big pete to get my tattoo done! Oh my god, this one hurt quite a bit. Right on the bone *shudders* But an hour later, a bit of blood and a lot of scrunched up, pained facial expressions and it was complete. I love it. Can't wait for my next one! Then we went to Portsmouth - Ended up going into Games Workshop because we've both been talking aout painting warcraft figurines. We eneded up battling each other and *Grins* I kicked his ass. So yeah, we're going to be geeks, get a few friends to come too and start attending a warhammer starters evening :P THEN we skipped off around shops, went to Gunwharf, Franky and Bennys. Had awesome tasting food (BBQ chicken with BBQ Ribs - side order of chips and garlic bread to share. Jack had a Meatball and pepperoni pizza)... and then we saw "Time Travelers Wife". Very good film, had to suck up all the emotions and try not to bawl my eyes out XD ... It didn't follow the book exactly, but it did get the ket points in - Can't say which one is my favourite... but i'd recommend both! Now im home. I've cleaned my tatoo... I've had a bath and im shamefully curled up on the sofa watching crap on TV. Don't want to go to work tomorrow >.> .. But darren is having a party at 6:30 so I'll be going there afterwards! Woop. Photos under cut! Hope everyone is enjoying their friday. Plans for the weekend?! Yazmin -xxx-

Hahaha. Myself, Mike, Jack, Tom, Kyle and Helen went to the beach this evening XD I brought my canon down with me (and my new wireless automatic shutter release... because my old one wouldn't work >.>) SO we had fun jumping off of benches, playing aerobeeeee, watching the sunset.. oh yeah and making stop motion clips *roars with laughter* There are more on Mike's Channel, so PLEASE check them out. In the mean time - here are a number of photos taken at the beach today (and some photos from this morning. I thought It'd be fun to chase butterflies ALL day long. Turns out it aint that fun!) I love friends XD Yazmin -xxx-

After getting back at about 1am this morning from Katie's party haha (thats a whole nother story), we finally fell asleep for about 3 hours before having to wake up, get ready and leave for Swindon. Skydiving for charity, sweethear' And it was amazing. With the help of everyone the sponsorship was really very high and I just want to say thank you to everyone for their help. It goes to a good cause at the Lennox children's cancer fund. So we arrived at Swindon Airfield at about 8:15am, after a LONG drive filled with scratch cards, mcdonalds breakfasts and starburst sweets :D We were all knackered, and my Aunty and Uncle decided to come along too! Signed up, went through a briefing and then.. my name was called. I was the first one up to jump *chuckles* I tell you what, the instructors are CUTE as hell and they have arm muscles that made my legs quite weak. He geared me up, strapped me tight, got in the plane, was secured very tightly to my instructor *grins* and had Ash, who was going to be filming me on my way down, in front of me with a cheshire cat grin. The plane took about 15 minutes to get to the correct (and shockingly, pee-your-pants type of high) height. shuffled over the edge (Ash dangling rather confidently on the side of the plane) and BAM! out of the plane, legs up, arms out - FLYING.. or rather FALLING gracefully through the air. The view was amazing, the feelings were exhilleration, everything, everything was PERFECT. And I can't WAIT to do it again hahah! After free falling for about 40 seconds at over 120mph, the parachute came out, flung us up.. and we just flew.... it was so peaceful and so cold. And then he thought it'd be fun to spin me around and around and around >.< AMAZING. We landed, got a certificate, photos taken - stripped off and thanked everyone for this life time experience. and my uncle cracked open the champagne! WOO. Photos under the cut!! Yazmin -xxx-
I can see both Jack and Myself in this SO much >.< I feel sick from excitement hahaa. I'm in the yellow/Grey top.. with black hair, obviously :D *Squeea* Yazmin -xxx-

I've just started my new journal (bought when i went out with Greg-ster... whilst chowing down on a bourbon milkshake), not sure where or how its going.. I've not long had a go at the first few pages.. but i've covered what was a blank black journal .. in poetry :3 More images under the cut. I hope you like them :] Page 1 so far ... still need to add a quote and a doddle :] Get there eventually Page two. Words to come Page 3 Me! They're all pretty similar which annoyed me >.> My timer thingy needs batteries. Stupid thing. I just saw a five second clip of Enter Shikari's new video.. and SAW JACK IN THE BACKGROUND! Yazmin -xxx-
I refuse to accept that Michael Jackson is... possibly dead. Yazmin -xxx-

I may not have had an amazing night sleep... but I couldn't help but smile when I woke up to my handsome man and my new second favourite fella (Jack's new cat - Puss puss, AKA Nick) laying next to me in bed... He'll probably hate that I've posted this... what with his hair all natural and curley ^_____^ num num. Yesterday Jack and I went out for Dinner at Nandos and then we went to the cinemas to see 'Angels And Demons' which was an amazing film :] Got home together quite late and went all cuddly until we fell asleep haha (*^_^*) Good times Yasmin -xxx-

We got up and ready for 3:15am - not very much sleep at all :] Stopped at Marks & Sparks Petrol Station for petrol and food - I thought a head and bought myself a chicken salad for lunch - and a nutrigrain bar for breakfast. We got to london at about 6 oclock-ish - Talked, snooped and laughed - Doors opened at 9:00am. We all spent a fair amount of money! Cosplayers were pretty good, not as good as last time though, which was a shame. Slight sun burn *Chuckles* everyone else ofcourse tanned. And we all got home - including Rachel's car which now has a HUGE scratch of white down the side, at exactly 5:00. Jack Slept over mine because I hadn't seen him ALL week :3 It was a cosy weekend. P.S - I totally saw Craig Charles from Red Dwarf haha :D Photos are under the cut - and believe me. There are a lot! Red Dwarf, baby ;D I have kitty ears! Mike and I are having BBQ / Water fight in about 2 weeks... and it's going to be fantastic! Yazmin -xxx-
I'm Home. I'm Knackered. But I've had an amazing weekend. More to come when I'm awake. Wahsed... and less grumpy!
